The paper deals with the reliability function of variable-length block codes over discrete memoryless channels (DMCs) with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses a communication and confirmation phase in the coding scheme, which is related to coding theory (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI). The proposed converse also involves analyzing the probability of error, which is a common theme in probability theory and statistics (cs.DS). Finally, the use of feedback in the coding scheme suggests a possible connection to networking and communication protocols (cs.NI).
